HEADWORD: Conferva
<hw>Con*fer"va</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Conferv⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., a kind of water
plant. See <er>Comfrey</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Any
unbranched, slender, green plant of the fresh-water algae. The word is
frequently used in a wider sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Confervaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
